The tomb marker was engraved with the name Charles A. Smith, a 20-month-old boy who passed away on August 6, 1870.

The bewildered homeowner called police, who seized the headstone and placed it in their evidence locker, where it has languished for more than a decade.

With no clues or tips to work off, investigators were completely stumped by the macabre find.

